svg.title: Mitteleuropa zur Zeit der Staufer
svg.desc:
A map in German of central Europe during the time of the Hohenstaufen Emperors, primarily showing the territories of the Holy Roman Empire and the Kingdom of Sicily.
The map is a vectorised version of one found in Professor G. Droysens Allgemeiner Historischer Handatlas, which was published in 1886 by R. Andrée Plate, and is now in the public domain. The source scan can be found at https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Droysens-26.jpg.
